    example: `If you invest $500 every month into an account with a 7% annual interest rate compounded monthly, you will accumulate approximately $609,985 after 30 years. This demonstrates how consistent, smaller contributions can grow substantially due to the cumulative effect of compounding interest over a long time horizon.`,
